description:
A behavioral economist is analyzing data from an Ultimatum Game experiment run via PEBL using the dataset at ~/pebl/data/ultimatum_data.csv. Analyze the responses to calculate acceptance rates across three offer tiers: unfair (offers 1, 2, and 3), fair (offers 4 and 5), and hyper_fair (offers 6, 7, 8, and 9). Determine the Minimum Acceptable Offer (MAO) for each participant, defined as the lowest offer amount (1-9) where the acceptance rate is at least 0.5; if no offer meets this criteria, the MAO is 10. Exclude any participant whose hyper_fair acceptance rate is strictly less than 0.8. Calculate the group means for the tier acceptance rates and MAOs of the valid participants. Produce a JSON report at ~/pebl/analysis/ultimatum_report.json following the structure provided below, including individual participant results and group averages.

{
  "participants": [
    {
      "id": "sub-01",
      "acceptance_rates": {"unfair": 0.13, "fair": 0.90, "hyper_fair": 1.0},
      "mao": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "sub-99",
      "excluded": true,
      "reason": "Hyper-fair acceptance rate < 0.8"
    }
  ],
  "group_means": {
    "unfair_acceptance": 0.18,
    "fair_acceptance": 0.89,
    "hyper_fair_acceptance": 0.98,
    "mean_mao": 3.45
  }
}
